    "media:imagetext": "1949\nFIRST COMMERCIAL PLANE TO USE 3,500-HORSEPOWER, 28-CYLINDER ENGINES\nWAS THE DOUBLE-DECKED BOEING STRATOCRUISER INTRODUCED IN 1949.\nWINGSPREAD WAS 141-FEET 3 INCHES; LENGTH,\n110-FEET 4 INCHES.\nTHE\nHUGE CLIPPER CRUISED AT A SPEED OF 320-MILES-PER-HOUR AND CARRIED\n47 SLEEPERETTE PASSENGERS, 61 REGULAR, AND 86 TOURIST. RATE OF\nCLIMB WAS 1,100 FEET PER MINUTE. LOUNGE WAS ON LOWER DECK AND\nREACHED BY A SPIRAL STAIRCASE; LOUNGE ACCOMMODATED 14 PASSENGERS.",
